NAME
    wc - count lines, words, and bytes

SYNOPSIS
    wc [OPTION]... [FILE]...

DESCRIPTION
    Print newline, word, and byte counts for each FILE, and a total line if
    more than one FILE is given. A word is a maximal run of non-whitespace.
    With no option, all three counts are printed.

    This is the unmodified GNU coreutils wc(1), ported to Horus and run as a
    ring-3 program from /bin/wc over the fs_server.

OPTIONS
    -l    print the newline count
    -w    print the word count
    -c    print the byte count
    -m    print the character count

    Run `wc --help` for the full option list.

EXIT STATUS
    0 on success, non-zero on error.

SEE ALSO
    cat(1), head(1), tail(1), hier(7)
